text:
table
CREATE TABLE ticket_support (
    ticket_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    student_name VARCHAR(255),
    programmer VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(255),
    phone_number VARCHAR(20),
    creator_id INTEGER,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    priority VARCHAR(20) CHECK (priority IN ('Urgent', 'Not urgent')),
    status VARCHAR(50) CHECK (status IN (
        'Cancelled', 'In Progress', 'Pending Approval', 'Paused', 'Completed',
        'Review Requested', 'Pending Acceptance', 'Processing Failed', 'Closed'
    )),
    result TEXT,
    description TEXT,
    ticket_group VARCHAR(50) CHECK (ticket_group IN (
        'Technical issue (student)', 'Technical issue (teacher)', 'Student absent',
        'Missing lesson materials', 'Reminder for student', 'Student off track',
        'Material error', 'Feedback on materials', 'Schedule error',
        'Payroll query', 'Lesson time change request'
    ))
);

create function find_teachers_matching_student(required_times text) returns text
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    required_times_json JSONB;
BEGIN
    required_times_json := required_times::jsonb;

    RETURN (SELECT jsonb_agg(
                           jsonb_build_object(
                                   'teacher_id', TI.teacher_id,
                                   'full_name', TI.full_name,
                                   'gender', TI.gender,
                                   'level_teacher', TI.level_teacher
                           )
                   )::TEXT
            FROM teacher_info TI
                     INNER JOIN (SELECT TZ.teacher_id,
                                        TZ.json_time_zone,
                                        TZ.updated_at,
                                        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY TZ.teacher_id ORDER BY TZ.updated_at DESC) AS rn
                                 FROM timezone_table TZ
                                 WHERE TZ.json_time_zone IS NOT NULL) TT ON TI.teacher_id = TT.teacher_id
                     LEFT JOIN course C ON TI.teacher_id = C.teacher_id
            WHERE TT.rn = 1
              AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1
                              FROM jsonb_array_elements(C.schedule::jsonb) AS course_times,
                                   jsonb_array_elements(required_times_json) AS required_entry
                              WHERE course_times ->> 'day' = required_entry ->> 'day'
                                AND (
                                  (course_times ->> 'start_time' < required_entry ->> 'end_time' AND
                                   course_times ->> 'end_time' > required_entry ->> 'start_time')
                                      AND NOT (
                                      course_times ->> 'end_time' = required_entry ->> 'start_time' OR
                                      course_times ->> 'start_time' = required_entry ->> 'end_time'
                                      )
                                  ))
              AND (SELECT bool_and(
                                  EXISTS (SELECT 1
                                          FROM jsonb_array_elements((TT.json_time_zone::jsonb) -> (entry ->> 'day')) AS day_times
                                          WHERE (
                                              day_times ->> 'start_time' <= entry ->> 'start_time' AND
                                              day_times ->> 'end_time' >= entry ->> 'end_time'
                                              )
                                             OR (
                                              day_times ->> 'start_time' <= entry ->> 'start_time' AND
                                              day_times ->> 'end_time' >= entry ->> 'start_time'
                                              )
                                             OR (
                                              day_times ->> 'start_time' <= entry ->> 'end_time' AND
                                              day_times ->> 'end_time' >= entry ->> 'end_time'
                                              ))
                          )
                   FROM jsonb_array_elements(required_times_json) AS entry));
END;
$$;

create function get_schedule_course_by_teacher_id(teacherid integer) returns text
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    result JSONB;
BEGIN
    SELECT jsonb_object_agg(day, schedules)
    INTO result
    FROM (SELECT schedule_item ->> 'day'                                     AS day,
                 jsonb_agg(jsonb_build_object('start_time', schedule_item ->> 'start_time', 'end_time',
                                              schedule_item ->> 'end_time')) AS schedules
          FROM (SELECT jsonb_array_elements(schedule::jsonb) AS schedule_item
                FROM course
                WHERE teacher_id = teacherId
                  AND status_course = 'active') AS schedule_expanded
          GROUP BY schedule_item ->> 'day') AS grouped_schedules;
    RETURN result::TEXT;
END;
$$;

create function get_list_class_session_by_course_id(p_course_id integer) returns text
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    result_json TEXT;
BEGIN

    SELECT jsonb_build_object(
                   'program_id', P.program_id,
                   'program_name', P.program_name,
                   'level_program', C.level_program,
                   'schedule', C.schedule,
                   'student_id', S.student_id,
                   'student_name', S.name_student,
                   'teacher_id', T.teacher_id,
                   'teacher_name', T.full_name,
                   'classes', jsonb_agg(
                           jsonb_build_object(
                                   'course_id', C.course_id,
                                   'teacher_id', T.teacher_id,
                                   'student_id', S.student_id,
                                   'teacher_name', T.full_name,
                                   'student_name', S.name_student,
                                   'class_session_id', CS.id_class_session,
                                   'going_date_time', CS.going_date_time,
                                   'duration', CS.duration,
                                   'status', CS.session_status
                           )
                              )
           )
    INTO result_json
    FROM course C
             INNER JOIN class_session CS ON C.course_id = CS.course_id
             INNER JOIN teacher_info T ON T.teacher_id = C.teacher_id
             INNER JOIN student S ON S.student_id = C.student_id
             INNER JOIN program P ON P.program_id = C.program_id
    WHERE C.course_id = p_course_id
    GROUP BY P.program_id, P.program_name, C.level_program, C.schedule, S.student_id, S.name_student, T.teacher_id,
             T.full_name;

    RETURN result_json;
END;
$$;

alter function get_list_class_session_by_course_id(integer) owner to postgres;

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.get_syllabus_id_data(syllabus_id_input integer)
 RETURNS text
 LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS $function$
DECLARE
    result JSON;
BEGIN
    SELECT json_agg(row_to_json(t))
    INTO result
    FROM (
        SELECT *
        FROM syllabus S
        LEFT JOIN syllabus_outline SO ON S.syllabus_id = SO.syllabus_id
        INNER JOIN book B ON B.book_id = SO.book_id
        INNER JOIN unit U ON U.unit_id = SO.unit_parent_id
        WHERE S.syllabus_id = syllabus_id_input -- L·ªçc theo syllabus_id
        ORDER BY SO.syllabus_id, SO.ordialnum
    ) t;

    RETURN result::TEXT;
END;
$function$

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.get_book_unit_data_by_book_id(p_book_id integer)
 RETURNS text
 LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS $function$
DECLARE
    result JSON;
BEGIN
    SELECT json_agg(row_to_json(t))
    INTO result
    FROM (
        SELECT
            B.book_id,
            B.book_name,
            B.link_document,         -- Th√¥ng tin t√†i li·ªáu t·ª´ b·∫£ng book
            U.unit_id,
            U.unit_name,
            U.ordialnum,
            U.unit_parent,
            UP.unit_name AS unit_parent_name -- L·∫•y t√™n c·ªßa unit_parent
        FROM
            book B
        INNER JOIN unit U ON U.book_id = B.book_id
        LEFT JOIN unit UP ON U.unit_parent = UP.unit_id::VARCHAR -- So s√°nh d∆∞·ªõi d·∫°ng VARCHAR
        WHERE
            B.book_id = p_book_id -- L·ªçc theo book_id
        ORDER BY
            U.ordialnum -- S·∫Øp x·∫øp theo th·ª© t·ª± c·ªßa ƒë∆°n v·ªã
    ) t;

    RETURN result::TEXT;
END;
$function$

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.update_or_create_book_and_unit(p_book_id integer, p_link_document text, p_units json)
 RETURNS void
 LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS $function$
BEGIN
    -- Update b·∫£ng book n·∫øu c√≥ link_document
    IF p_link_document IS NOT NULL THEN
        UPDATE book
        SET link_document = p_link_document
        WHERE book_id = p_book_id;
    END IF;

    -- X√≥a t·∫•t c·∫£ c√°c unit li√™n quan ƒë·∫øn book_id
    DELETE FROM unit WHERE book_id = p_book_id;

    -- Th√™m m·ªõi to√†n b·ªô c√°c ƒë∆°n v·ªã (unit) t·ª´ p_units
    INSERT INTO unit (unit_name, book_id, ordialnum, unit_parent)
    SELECT 
        unit.unit_name, 
        COALESCE(unit.book_id, p_book_id), -- ƒê·∫£m b·∫£o l·∫•y gi√° tr·ªã book_id t·ª´ JSON ho·∫∑c t·ª´ tham s·ªë p_book_id
        unit.ordialnum, 
        unit.unit_parent
    FROM json_populate_recordset(NULL::unit, p_units) AS unit;
END;
$function$

create function get_list_class_session_by_course_id(p_course_id integer) returns text
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    result_json TEXT;
BEGIN

    SELECT jsonb_build_object(
                   'program_id', P.program_id,
                   'program_name', P.program_name,
                   'level_program', C.level_program,
                   'schedule', C.schedule,
                   'student_id', S.student_id,
                   'student_name', S.name_student,
                   'teacher_id', T.teacher_id,
                   'teacher_name', T.full_name,
                   'classes', jsonb_agg(
                           jsonb_build_object(
                                   'course_id', C.course_id,
                                   'teacher_id', CS.teacher_id,
                                   'student_id', S.student_id,
                                   'teacher_name', (SELECT full_name FROM teacher_info TI WHERE TI.teacher_id = CS.teacher_id),
                                   'student_name', S.name_student,
                                   'class_session_id', CS.id_class_session,
                                   'going_date_time', CS.going_date_time,
                                   'duration', CS.duration,
                                   'status', CS.session_status,
                                   'pic', CS.pic,
                                   'pending_date', CS.pending_date,
                                   'pending_reason', CS.pending_reason,
                                   'topic', CS.topic,
                                   'content_speaking_goal', CS.content_speaking_goal,
                                   'session_number', CS.session_number,
                                   'lesson_report', CS.lesson_report,
                                   'coach_plan_next_lesson', CS.coach_plan_next_lesson,
                                   'note', CS.note,
                                   'document_path', CS.document_path,
                                   'observation_report', CS.observation_report
                           )
                              )
           )
    INTO result_json
    FROM course C
             INNER JOIN class_session CS ON C.course_id = CS.course_id
             INNER JOIN teacher_info T ON T.teacher_id = C.teacher_id
             INNER JOIN student S ON S.student_id = C.student_id
             INNER JOIN program P ON P.program_id = C.program_id
    WHERE C.course_id = p_course_id
    GROUP BY P.program_id, P.program_name, C.level_program, C.schedule, S.student_id, S.name_student, T.teacher_id,
             T.full_name;

    RETURN result_json;
END;
$$;

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.update_student_circle_data(p_student_circle_id integer, p_request_create_course jsonb)
 RETURNS void
 LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS $function$
DECLARE
    current_request jsonb; -- D·ªØ li·ªáu hi·ªán t·∫°i c·ªßa request_create_course
    session_data jsonb; -- T·ª´ng ph·∫ßn t·ª≠ trong class_sessions
    updated_sessions jsonb := '[]'::jsonb; -- Danh s√°ch class_sessions sau khi x·ª≠ l√Ω
    going_date_time TIMESTAMP; -- Bi·∫øn l∆∞u going_date_time
    account_classin_id INT; -- Bi·∫øn l∆∞u account_classin_id
BEGIN
    -- L·∫•y d·ªØ li·ªáu hi·ªán t·∫°i c·ªßa request_create_course t·ª´ b·∫£ng student_circle
    SELECT request_create_course INTO current_request
    FROM student_circle
    WHERE student_circle_id = p_student_circle_id;

    -- Ki·ªÉm tra n·∫øu current_request kh√¥ng t·ªìn t·∫°i
    IF current_request IS NULL THEN
        RAISE NOTICE 'No request_create_course found for student_circle_id: %', p_student_circle_id;
        RETURN;
    END IF;

    -- L·∫∑p qua t·ª´ng ph·∫ßn t·ª≠ trong class_sessions
    FOR session_data IN SELECT * FROM jsonb_array_elements(current_request->'class_sessions')
    LOOP
        -- Tr√≠ch xu·∫•t th√¥ng tin c·∫ßn thi·∫øt
        going_date_time := (session_data->>'going_date_time')::TIMESTAMP;

        -- L·∫•y account_classin_id t·ª´ b·∫£ng class_session n·∫øu t·ªìn t·∫°i
        SELECT account_classin_id INTO account_classin_id
        FROM class_session
        WHERE going_date_time = going_date_time;

        -- Th√™m account_classin_id v√†o session_data n·∫øu t·ªìn t·∫°i
        IF account_classin_id IS NOT NULL THEN
            session_data := jsonb_set(session_data, '{account_classin_id}', to_jsonb(account_classin_id));
        END IF;

        -- Th√™m session_data ƒë√£ c·∫≠p nh·∫≠t v√†o updated_sessions
        updated_sessions := updated_sessions || session_data;

        -- C·∫≠p nh·∫≠t b·∫£ng class_session v·ªõi account_classin_id
        UPDATE class_session
        SET account_classin_id = account_classin_id
        WHERE going_date_time = going_date_time;
    END LOOP;

    -- C·∫≠p nh·∫≠t ch·ªâ tr∆∞·ªùng class_sessions trong request_create_course
    current_request := jsonb_set(current_request, '{class_sessions}', updated_sessions);

    -- C·∫≠p nh·∫≠t l·∫°i request_create_course v√†o b·∫£ng student_circle
    UPDATE student_circle
    SET request_create_course = current_request,
        is_qc_done = TRUE
    WHERE student_circle_id = p_student_circle_id;

    -- Log k·∫øt qu·∫£ cu·ªëi c√πng
    RAISE NOTICE 'Updated request_create_course and is_qc_done for student_circle_id: %', p_student_circle_id;
END;
$function$

create function get_teacher_schedule() returns jsonb
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    result JSONB;
BEGIN
    WITH tmp AS (SELECT DISTINCT ON (teacher_id) teacher_id, json_time_zone, updated_at
                 FROM timezone_table
                 ORDER BY teacher_id, updated_at DESC),
         tmp2 AS (SELECT TI.teacher_id, TI.full_name, T.json_time_zone
                  FROM teacher_info TI
                           LEFT JOIN tmp T ON T.teacher_id = TI.teacher_id
                  WHERE TI.teacher_id IS NOT NULL
                  ORDER BY TI.teacher_id),
         formatted_data AS (SELECT teacher_id,
                                   TRIM(TO_CHAR(going_date_time, 'Day'))                                  AS day_of_week,
                                   TO_CHAR(going_date_time, 'HH24:MI')                                    AS start_time,
                                   TO_CHAR(going_date_time + (duration * INTERVAL '1 minute'), 'HH24:MI') AS end_time
                            FROM class_session
                            WHERE going_date_time >= NOW()),
         grouped_json AS (SELECT teacher_id,
                                 day_of_week,
                                 JSONB_AGG(
                                         DISTINCT JSONB_BUILD_OBJECT(
                                         'start_time', start_time,
                                         'end_time', end_time
                                                  )
                                 ) AS times
                          FROM formatted_data
                          GROUP BY teacher_id, day_of_week),
         final_json_prep AS (SELECT teacher_id,
                                    day_of_week,
                                    times
                             FROM grouped_json),
         final_json AS (SELECT teacher_id,
                               JSONB_OBJECT_AGG(day_of_week, times) AS json_schedule
                        FROM final_json_prep
                        GROUP BY teacher_id),
         tmp3 AS (SELECT T2.teacher_id,
                         T2.full_name,
                         T2.json_time_zone,
                         T3.json_schedule
                  FROM tmp2 T2
                           LEFT JOIN final_json T3 ON T2.teacher_id = T3.teacher_id),
         tmp4 AS (SELECT SBT.teacher_id,
                         TRIM(TO_CHAR(SBT.going_date_time, 'Day'))                   AS day_of_week,
                         TO_CHAR(SBT.going_date_time, 'HH24:MI')                     AS start_time,
                         TO_CHAR(SBT.going_date_time + INTERVAL '1 hour', 'HH24:MI') AS end_time

create function check_teacher_availability(p_going_date_time timestamp without time zone, p_teacher_id integer) returns boolean
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    is_available BOOLEAN;
BEGIN
    WITH selected_json AS (
        SELECT json_time_zone::jsonb AS json_data
        FROM timezone_table
        WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
        ORDER BY updated_at DESC
        LIMIT 1
    ),
    parsed_json AS (
        SELECT
            jsonb_object_keys(json_data) AS day_name,
            jsonb_array_elements(json_data->jsonb_object_keys(json_data)) AS time_range
        FROM selected_json
    )
    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM parsed_json
            WHERE
                LOWER(TRIM(day_name)) = LOWER(TRIM(TO_CHAR(p_going_date_time, 'Day')))
                AND (time_range->>'start_time')::TIME <= p_going_date_time::TIME
                AND (time_range->>'end_time')::TIME >= (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '60 minutes')::TIME
        )
        THEN TRUE
        ELSE FALSE
    END INTO is_available;

    IF is_available = FALSE THEN
        RETURN FALSE;
    END IF;

    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM class_session
            WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
              AND session_status = 'upcoming'
              AND going_date_time::DATE = p_going_date_time::DATE
              AND (
                  (going_date_time + duration * INTERVAL '1 minute') < (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '60 minutes')
                  AND going_date_time > (p_going_date_time - INTERVAL '60 minutes')
              )
        )
        THEN FALSE
        ELSE TRUE
    END INTO is_available;

    IF is_available = FALSE THEN
        RETURN FALSE;
    END IF;

    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM session_book_test
            WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
              AND session_status = 'upcoming'
              AND going_date_time::DATE = p_going_date_time::DATE
              AND (
                  (going_date_time + INTERVAL '60 minutes') < (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '60 minutes')
                  AND going_date_time > (p_going_date_time - INTERVAL '60 minutes')
              )
        )
        THEN FALSE
        ELSE TRUE
    END INTO is_available;

    RETURN is_available;
END;
$$;

alter function check_teacher_availability(timestamp, integer) owner to postgres;

create function check_teacher_availability(p_going_date_time timestamp without time zone, p_teacher_id integer) returns boolean
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    is_available BOOLEAN;
BEGIN
    WITH selected_json AS (
        SELECT json_time_zone::jsonb AS json_data
        FROM timezone_table
        WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
        ORDER BY updated_at DESC
        LIMIT 1
    ),
    parsed_json AS (
        SELECT
            jsonb_object_keys(json_data) AS day_name,
            jsonb_array_elements(json_data->jsonb_object_keys(json_data)) AS time_range
        FROM selected_json
    )
    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM parsed_json
            WHERE
                LOWER(TRIM(day_name)) = LOWER(TRIM(TO_CHAR(p_going_date_time, 'Day')))
                AND (time_range->>'start_time')::TIME <= p_going_date_time::TIME
                AND (time_range->>'end_time')::TIME >= (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '60 minutes')::TIME
        )
        THEN TRUE
        ELSE FALSE
    END INTO is_available;

    IF is_available = FALSE THEN
        RETURN FALSE;
    END IF;

    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM class_session
            WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
              AND session_status = 'upcoming'
              AND going_date_time::DATE = p_going_date_time::DATE
              AND (
                  ((going_date_time + duration * INTERVAL '1 minute') < (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '60 minutes')
                  AND going_date_time > (p_going_date_time - INTERVAL '60 minutes'))
                  OR going_date_time::TIMESTAMP = p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP
              )
        )
        THEN FALSE
        ELSE TRUE
    END INTO is_available;

    IF is_available = FALSE THEN
        RETURN FALSE;
    END IF;

    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM session_book_test
            WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
              AND session_status = 'upcoming'
              AND going_date_time::DATE = p_going_date_time::DATE
              AND (
                  ((going_date_time + INTERVAL '60 minutes') < (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '60 minutes')
                  AND going_date_time > (p_going_date_time - INTERVAL '60 minutes'))
                  OR going_date_time::TIMESTAMP = p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP
              )
        )
        THEN FALSE
        ELSE TRUE
    END INTO is_available;

    RETURN is_available;
END;
$$;

create function check_teacher_availability(p_going_date_time timestamp without time zone, p_teacher_id integer) returns boolean
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    is_available BOOLEAN;
    start_of_week DATE;
BEGIN

    start_of_week := date_trunc('week', p_going_date_time)::DATE;

    WITH selected_json AS (
        SELECT json_time_zone::jsonb->'book_test_session'->(start_of_week::TEXT) AS json_data
        FROM timezone_table
        WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
        ORDER BY updated_at DESC
        LIMIT 1
    ),
    parsed_json AS (
        SELECT
            jsonb_object_keys(json_data) AS day_name,
            jsonb_array_elements(json_data->jsonb_object_keys(json_data)) AS time_range
        FROM selected_json
    )
    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM parsed_json
            WHERE
                LOWER(TRIM(day_name)) = LOWER(TRIM(TO_CHAR(p_going_date_time, 'Day')))
                AND (time_range->>'start_time')::TIME <= p_going_date_time::TIME
                AND (time_range->>'end_time')::TIME >= (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '30 minutes')::TIME
        )
        THEN TRUE
        ELSE FALSE
    END INTO is_available;

    IF is_available = FALSE THEN
        RETURN FALSE;
    END IF;

    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM class_session
            WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
              AND session_status = 'upcoming'
              AND going_date_time::DATE = p_going_date_time::DATE
              AND (
                  ((going_date_time + duration * INTERVAL '1 minute') < (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '30 minutes')
                  AND going_date_time > (p_going_date_time - INTERVAL '30 minutes'))
                  OR going_date_time::TIMESTAMP = p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP
              )
        )
        THEN FALSE
        ELSE TRUE
    END INTO is_available;

    IF is_available = FALSE THEN
        RETURN FALSE;
    END IF;

    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM session_book_test
            WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
              AND session_status = 'upcoming'
              AND going_date_time::DATE = p_going_date_time::DATE
              AND (
                  ((going_date_time + INTERVAL '30 minutes') < (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '30 minutes')
                  AND going_date_time > (p_going_date_time - INTERVAL '30 minutes'))
                  OR going_date_time::TIMESTAMP = p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP
              )
        )
        THEN FALSE
        ELSE TRUE
    END INTO is_available;

    RETURN is_available;
END;
$$;

    ),
    final_book_json AS (
        SELECT
            teacher_id,
            JSONB_OBJECT_AGG(day_of_week, times) AS json_book_teacher
        FROM final_book_json_prep
        GROUP BY teacher_id
    ),
    combined_data AS (
        SELECT
            tmp3.teacher_id,
            tmp3.full_name,
            tmp3.json_time_zone,
            tmp3.json_schedule::TEXT,
            final_book_json.json_book_teacher::TEXT
        FROM tmp3
        LEFT JOIN final_book_json ON tmp3.teacher_id = final_book_json.teacher_id
    )
    SELECT jsonb_agg(combined_data)
    INTO result
    FROM combined_data;

    RETURN result;
END;
$$;

create function check_teacher_availability(p_going_date_time timestamp without time zone, p_teacher_id integer) returns boolean
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    is_available BOOLEAN;
    start_of_week DATE;
BEGIN
    start_of_week := date_trunc('week', p_going_date_time)::DATE;

    WITH selected_json AS (
        SELECT json_time_zone::jsonb->'book_test_session'->(start_of_week::TEXT) AS json_data
        FROM timezone_table
        WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
        ORDER BY updated_at DESC
        LIMIT 1
    ),
    parsed_json AS (
        SELECT
            jsonb_object_keys(json_data) AS day_name,
            jsonb_array_elements(json_data->jsonb_object_keys(json_data)) AS time_range
        FROM selected_json
    )
    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM parsed_json
            WHERE
                LOWER(TRIM(day_name)) = LOWER(TRIM(TO_CHAR(p_going_date_time, 'Day')))
                AND (time_range->>'start_time')::TIME <= p_going_date_time::TIME
                AND (time_range->>'end_time')::TIME >= (p_going_date_time + INTERVAL '30 minutes')::TIME
        )
        THEN TRUE
        ELSE FALSE
    END
    INTO is_available;

    IF is_available = FALSE THEN
        RETURN FALSE;
    END IF;

    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM class_session
            WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
              AND session_status = 'upcoming'
              AND going_date_time::DATE = p_going_date_time::DATE
              AND (
                  (
                      (going_date_time + duration * INTERVAL '1 minute' > p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP
                           AND going_date_time + duration * INTERVAL '1 minute' < p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '30 minutes')
                      OR (
                          p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '30 minutes' > going_date_time
                          AND p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '30 minutes' < going_date_time + duration * INTERVAL '1 minute')
                  )
                  OR going_date_time::TIMESTAMP = p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP
              )
        )
        THEN FALSE
        ELSE TRUE
    END
    INTO is_available;

    -- N·∫øu tr√πng v·ªõi class_session -> Kh√¥ng kh·∫£ d·ª•ng
    IF is_available = FALSE THEN
        RETURN FALSE;
    END IF;

    SELECT CASE
        WHEN EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM session_book_test
            WHERE teacher_id = p_teacher_id
              AND session_status = 'upcoming'
              AND going_date_time::DATE = p_going_date_time::DATE
              AND (
                  (
                      (going_date_time + INTERVAL '30 minutes' > p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP
                           AND going_date_time + INTERVAL '30 minutes' < p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '30 minutes')
                      OR (
                          p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '30 minutes' > going_date_time
                          AND p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP + INTERVAL '30 minutes' < going_date_time + INTERVAL '30 minutes')
                  )
                  OR going_date_time::TIMESTAMP = p_going_date_time::TIMESTAMP
              )
        )
        THEN FALSE
        ELSE TRUE
    END
    INTO is_available;

    RETURN is_available;
END;
$$;

create function get_syllabus_data() returns text
    language plpgsql
as
$$
DECLARE
    result JSON;
BEGIN
    SELECT json_agg(row_to_json(t))
    INTO result
    FROM (SELECT SO.syllabus_outline_id,
                 S.syllabus_id,
                 S.syllabus_name,
                 SO.ordialnum,
                 B.book_id,
                 B.book_name,
                 U.unit_id,
                 U.unit_name,
                 SO.unit_parent_id,
                 SO.unit_parent_name,
                 SO.content,
                 SO.topic_name,
                 SO.note
          FROM syllabus S
                   LEFT JOIN syllabus_outline SO ON S.syllabus_id = SO.syllabus_id
                   LEFT JOIN book B ON B.book_id = SO.book_id
                   LEFT JOIN unit U ON U.unit_id = SO.unit_parent_id
          ORDER BY S.syllabus_id, SO.ordialnum) t;

    RETURN result::TEXT;
END;
$$;

alter function get_syllabus_data() owner to postgres;
